The paper discusses nonparametric approaches to CCA, which are related to machine learning and statistical inference. Specifically, the paper builds on recent developments in high-dimensional nonparametric regression, which is a topic in machine learning and statistics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which are also related to machine learning. Additionally, the paper applies the proposed methods to genomic data, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
